  "text": "All clinical studies were approved by the Yale Human Investigation Committee. Kindreds PHA15 and PHA16 have been described previously (5). Although not known to be related, these families live in the same village in northwestern Spain and were found to carry the identical R537X disease-causing mutation. We extended these pedigrees by recruiting relatives of known adPHA1 carriers. We prospectively screened individuals in these pedigrees for clinical indices of reninangiotensin-aldosterone system activity, including BP, serum chemistries, and aldosterone levels. At the time of study, no individuals were taking sodium supplements or BP medications. They subsequently were genotyped for the presence of the R537X mutation. BP was measured in the seated position. Blood for serum chemistry and aldosterone levels was drawn in the seated position. Genomic DNA was prepared, and single-strand conformation polymorphism was performed as described previously [CITATION_1] .",
